comments: Barnes (SAC) maintains a legal guarding position on Morris Sr. (NYK) when he loses his balance and falls to the floor during his drive.
Randle (NYK) extends his arm into Joseph's (SAC) front during the drive and the contact dislodges him from his legal guarding position.
Randle (NYK) delivers contact to Barnes' (SAC) body during the upward shooting motion on his shot attempt.
Morris Sr. (NYK) establishes himself in a legal screening position in Holmes' (SAC) path and he is firming up when the contact occurs during the screen.
Holmes (SAC) reaches in and makes contact with the ball during Randle's (NYK) drive.
Randle (NYK) regains possession of the ball and it does not touch the out of bounds line.
Holmes (SAC) legally defends Randle's (NYK) jump shot attempt.
Holmes (SAC) reaches in with one hand that does not make contact to Barrett (NYK) but he re-reaches with his other hand and makes contact with the ball during the drive.

Bogdanovic's (SAC) arms are retreating back into a legal position when the contact occurs to Payton's (NYK) left arm. The marginal contact occurs as Payton removes his off arm from the ball during the upward shooting motion on his shot attempt.
Joseph (SAC) initiates some contact to Barrett's (NYK) body during the drive but he is able to move through the marginal contact and continue his drive.
Joseph (SAC) makes contact to Barrett's (NYK) wrist after the release that does not affect his driving shot attempt. The contact is deemed incidental.
Holmes (SAC) delivers contact to Payton (NYK) during the screen and the contact affects his ability to defend.
Hield (SAC) slightly extends his arm into Morris Sr.'s (NYK) body during the loose ball but the contact is marginal.
Holmes (SAC) initiates contact to Morris Sr. (NYK) that affects his ability to get to the inbound pass.
Randle (NYK) and Hield (SAC) mutually engage in marginal contact. Randle (NYK) does not dislodge Hield (SAC) from his legally obtained position during the inbound.
Barnes (SAC) initiates contact to Randle (NYK) that affects his ability to gather the inbound pass.
